---
// src/components/SeoContent.astro
---
<article class="seo-container" id="seo-info-drawer">
  <div class="seo-drawer-backdrop" id="seo-drawer-close-btn-backdrop"></div>
  <div class="seo-drawer-panel">
    <div class="seo-drawer-header">
      <h2 class="seo-drawer-title">About Typeframe & Design Science</h2>
      <button type="button" class="seo-drawer-close" id="seo-drawer-close-btn" aria-label="Close guide">×</button>
    </div>
    
    <div class="seo-drawer-scrollable">
      <section class="seo-section">
        <h3>Why Typography Matters: The Science of Visual Fluency</h3>
        <p>
          Research in cognitive psychology shows that <strong>visual fluency</strong>—the ease with which information is processed visually—directly influences how readers evaluate content. When text is presented with optimal line spacing, clean margins, and balanced contrast, the brain requires less cognitive energy to parse it. This is known as the <em>Cognitive Load Reduction</em> principle.
        </p>
        <p>
          Furthermore, studies demonstrate that articles or social posts with elegant layout structures and balanced whitespace enjoy <strong>up to a 75% higher read-through rate</strong> and significantly stronger user retention. Beautiful typographic hierarchy establishes trust and enhances perceived credibility immediately.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="seo-section">
        <h3>How to Optimize Your Typographic Graphics</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Leverage Hierarchy:</strong> Keep headings large and bold (at least 1.5x of body text size) to guide the reader's eye first.</li>
          <li><strong>Mind the Leading:</strong> Maintain line heights (leading) between 1.3 and 1.6 to avoid lines crowding each other, which increases tracking comfort.</li>
          <li><strong>High-Contrast Atmosphere:</strong> Ensure text color contrasts strongly with your background. Use mesh glows or dark paper textures to add depth without distracting from the text.</li>
          <li><strong>Sizing for the Channel:</strong> Match your dimension templates to the destination platform (e.g., Square 1:1 for Instagram/LinkedIn feeds, 16:9 landscape for Twitter/X).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="seo-section">
        <h3>Key Features of Typeframe</h3>
        <div class="seo-features-grid">
          <div class="feature-item">
            <strong>Rich Text & Markdown:</strong> Style specific words in bold, italic, or colored span highlights directly within the editor.
          </div>
          <div class="feature-item">
            <strong>Generative Backdrops:</strong> Choose from solid fills, gradients, mesh glows, frosted glass, or subtle linen paper grain.
          </div>
          <div class="feature-item">
            <strong>Drag & Nudge Blocks:</strong> Freely position your text, resize boundaries, or use arrow keys for pixel-perfect layout adjustments.
          </div>
          <div class="feature-item">
            <strong>Scalable Exports:</strong> Download high-fidelity PNG, JPEG, WebP, or vector SVG assets instantly.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="seo-section">
        <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
        <div class="seo-faq-accordion">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What is Typeframe?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              Typeframe is a free, modern typographic studio designed to convert quotes, tweets, and text into gorgeous social media graphics. It provides professional font templates, customizable backgrounds, and instant, high-quality rendering.
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Is Typeframe free to use?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              Yes, Typeframe is completely free. There are no limits, no watermarks, and no sign-ups required. You can export unlimited graphics for personal or commercial use.
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">How does local processing work?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              Typeframe operates entirely in your browser. All image renders, custom photo uploads, and configurations are computed locally on your device via HTML5 Canvas. Your text and images are never uploaded to any remote server, guaranteeing absolute privacy.
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Can I copy the image directly to my clipboard?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              Yes! You can use the "Copy Image" button to save the generated graphic directly to your system clipboard, letting you paste it directly into Twitter/X, LinkedIn, Slack, or other platforms without having to download a file.
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What formatting options are supported?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              Typeframe supports Plain, Rich (HTML-based tags like <code>&lt;b&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;i&gt;</code>, or custom text colors), and Markdown modes. You can highlight specific phrases and apply bold or italic styles using standard markdown shortcuts.
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
